name: arlbench
description:
The ARLBench Performance Dataset
	

ARLBench is a benchmark for hyperparameter optimization in Reinforcement Learning. 
Since we performed several thousand runs on the benchmark to find meaningful HPO test settings in RL, we collect them in this dataset for future use.
These runs could be used to meta-learn information about the hyperparameter landscape or warmstart HPO tools.
In detail, it contains each 10 runs for PPO, DQN and SAC respectively on the Atari-5 environments, four… See the full description on the dataset page: https://huggingface.co/datasets/autorl-org/arlbench.
